 (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) restrictions to increased production among which the most 
 important are wearing away due to not enough water and soil conservation 
 programmes, high human and animals population pressures on farming-based land, and repeated and (constant/not going away) drought especially in the northern 
 and northeastern areas. These restrictions limit directly the opportunities 
 of development efforts, especially in the poor (person) farming part/area where 
 individual farmers' efforts can not lessen their effects. 
