 INVESTMENT IN AGRICULTURE 
 
 The central importance of farming to the nation is stressed in the 
 national development plan of Ethiopia (NRDCjCPSC, 1983). The plan has 
 admitted/recognized/responded to the need to increase and (branch out into different things) farming-based output, to 
 (accomplish or gain with effort) independence in food supply, and to raise (away from cities) incomes and living 
 standards. To (accomplish or gain with effort) this, big public investment in farming is of 
 most important importance. Viewed over time, maybe the most famous aspect 
 of public investment in farming is that its after- 1975 share is greater than 
 its pre-1975 share (Table 11). The socialist Government created its first 
 ten-year long-term plan in 1981 for the period 1984 to 1994 (NRDCjCPSC, 
